# Backend Development Rules

## Project Structure

- Main entry point: [zen-server/src/main.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/main.rs)
- Features in [zen-server/src/features/](mdc:zen-server/src/features/)
- Infra in [zen-server/src/infra/](mdc:zen-server/src/infra/)
- Common utilities in [zen-server/src/common/](mdc:zen-server/src/common/)
- Middleware in [zen-server/src/middleware/](mdc:zen-server/src/middleware/)
- Migrations in [zen-server/migrations/](mdc:zen-server/migrations/)

## Dependency Management

- Never directly modify `Cargo.toml` to add dependencies; use `cargo add`.
- Obtain user confirmation before adding new dependencies.
- Keep `Cargo.lock` under version control.

## Error Handling

- Follow patterns in [zen-server/src/common/error.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/common/error.rs).
- Return explicit errors; avoid silent fallback branches.

## API Conventions

- API response fields should use `camelCase`.
- Handler naming follows REST semantics (`list_*`, `get_*`, `create_*`, `update_*`, `delete_*`).
- Keep response structure consistent with existing `ApiResponse`.

## Code Organization

- Each feature should use:
    - `mod.rs` for routing assembly
    - `handler.rs` for request/response only
    - `service.rs` for orchestration
    - `repo.rs` for SQL/persistence
    - `types.rs` for row/entity/request/response/query types
- Follow the pattern in [zen-server/src/features/system/user/](mdc:zen-server/src/features/system/user/).

## Database Integration

- Use pool and infra helpers in [zen-server/src/infra/db.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/infra/db.rs).
- Keep SQL in `repo.rs`, avoid `SELECT *`, and use transactions when needed.

## Authentication & Authorization

- Shared JWT codec, claims, extractor, and `auth_middleware` live under [zen-core/src/auth/](mdc:zen-core/src/auth/) (for example [zen-core/src/auth/jwt.rs](mdc:zen-core/src/auth/jwt.rs) and [zen-core/src/auth/middleware.rs](mdc:zen-core/src/auth/middleware.rs)).
- Route permission extension (`RouterExt`) lives in [zen-core/src/permission/route.rs](mdc:zen-core/src/permission/route.rs).
- Do not re-implement JWT or route permission helpers in `zen-server/`; reuse `zen-core` and wire secrets/runtime in `zen-server` infra only (see `docs/backend-guide.md`).
- Password hashing in [zen-server/src/infra/password.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/infra/password.rs).
- Permission cache and menu sync in [zen-server/src/infra/permission.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/infra/permission.rs).
- App JWT wiring and codec singleton: [zen-server/src/infra/auth_runtime.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/infra/auth_runtime.rs) (composed in [zen-server/src/infra/app.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/infra/app.rs)).

## Logging

- Use structured logging throughout backend code.
- Log middleware in [zen-server/src/middleware/log.rs](mdc:zen-server/src/middleware/log.rs).
